entry.title: [EnumSet] Refactor constructor usages
entry.content:
TL;DR: EnumSet variadic template ctor is being replaced with ctor

accepting std::initializer_list. Some usages are not compatible and this

CL updates them.



Implicit EnumValue->EnumSet conversions and direct calls of variadic

template constructor (e.g. EnumSet(value1,...)) don't work with

initializer_list ctor. This CL replaces them with:

1. [Only variables initializations] EnumSet set = {value1, ...};

2. [Only inside macro invocations] EnumSet({value1, ...})

3. Implicit construction from initializer_list (note that this is a

special case of implicit conversion, intentionally supported in STL

and by clang-tidy warnings):

foo(value1) -> foo({value1});

foo(EnumSet(value1, ...)) -> foo({value1, ...});

4. EnumSet(value1, ...) -> EnumSet{value1, ...};



Note that 3 and 4 are mostly the same, in most places I made a choice

that resembles pre-existing code closer (exceptions are mostly usages of

Sync EnumSets).



Motivation:

EnumSet variadic template constructor is defective in a sense that it

allows code like this to compile:

using ModelTypeSet = EnumSet;

void foo(ModelTypeSet set);

foo(ModelType()); // Typo, intended to pass empty ModelTypeSet.



The problem is that constructor is not explicit. Simply making it

explicit will disallow nice STL-like usage:

class C {

ModelTypeSet set = {HISTORY, BOOKMARKS};

};



STL and other containers under base/containers avoid this problem by

using std::initializer_list, this refactoring does the same for EnumSet.



This CL was uploaded by git cl split.



R=dcheng@chromium.org

entry.title: dlp: file manager APIs for notification callbacks
entry.content:
Policy notifications are shown in case of warnings or errors (blocked

files). In case of multiple affected files, the notification has a

"Review" button to show a more detailed view in a dialog over the app.

In case of a single file in warning, the user should be able to "accept"

the warning directly from the notification, i.e. continue the action.



The CL adds file manager private APIs and extension functions that

handle these three activities. The extension functions currently do not

do anything, but will in the future call `FilesPolicyNotificationManager`

to actually show the dialog / resume the IO task. This class will keep

track of all the necessary information, identified by the IOTask ID.

This ID is passed to the Files App in each status update, and passed via

the new APIs back to the `FilesPolicyNotificationManager`.

entry.title: Upstream offer save card with the same last four but different
entry.content:
expiration dates.



This CL supports below workflow:

1. Tried to find a server card which matches extracted credit card

candidate with same last four and the same expiration date the

user has saved.

2. Doesn't offer to save the card if one is found as described above.



This will result in more accurate upload saves, especially in the

American Express case, as multiple American Express cards for the same

user can have the same last 4 digits. The 5th digit is usually

different, so we need an additional check to the last four digit check

to ensure we are saving the proper cards. Currently, we do not upload

save as many American Express server cards as we should, due to thinking

more of them are server cards that are not. And in the VCN case, we can

accidentally enroll the incorrect American Express server card into VCN.

These changes will fix those issues.

entry.title: show final try results at timeout
entry.content:
When the importer times out waiting for the try job results (3 hours),

there isn't a way to tell from the logs which builder is the issue.

Checking the CL shows all as complete (probably one finished after

the designated time). Adding the final result will help pinpoint the

entry.content:
ChromeFeatureList#getFieldTrialParamsForFeature() does not return test

override values at the moment unless native is loaded - in which

case they will be returned due to being added to the command line.



This makes test overrides only be honored in instrumentation tests

for getFieldTrialParamsForFeature(), but not in Robolectric tests.

code usage is from AllCachedFieldTrialParameters, the API could be

used by other code, and it would be surprising to find that it

doesn't support test overrides while individual

getFieldTrialParamByFeature() and similar methods honor these overrides.



Another motivation is to simplify another refactor by removing the JNI

mocking from CachedFieldTrialParameterUnitTest.

entry.title: Remove origin from AutofillProfile.
entry.content:
The distinction between verified and unverified profiles has recently

been removed from Autofill ([1] and bug for context). This makes the

origin irrelevant for AutofillProfile. This CL removes

AutofillProfile::origin_ and AutofillProfile::IsVerified().



Both the origin and IsVerified() are inherited from AutofillProfile's

base class, AutofillDataModel. This class is also used for credit cards

and IBANs. Credit cards still distinguish between (un)verified profiles,

but IBANs never introduced the concept of an origin. For this reason,

origin and IsVerified() (+ tests) are moved from AutofillDataModel

to CreditCard.



Follow-up CLs remove the origin from the database, in an effort to unify

the data model [2].



[1] https://docs.google.com/document/d/1qIUjKcC7uotwOoXil3xyweHqLKNV9Hw0xXxyXc25JPs/edit#heading=h.wcygfssstf1k

[2] https://docs.google.com/document/d/18Zg5V3uVRseCIFhwQ0r2sGsCFW9vkoYDl4d-uJXsYw0/edit?usp=sharing&resourcekey=0-f79nMmTTOo6irPIuT-kKkQ

entry.title: Allow programmatic clicks on AX nodes created from CSS content property
entry.content:
Previously, assistive tech trying to click an AX Node by calling

DoDefaultAction() would do nothing if the AX Node was created from a

layout tree traversal in AXNodeObject::AddChildrenImpl(). This is

because these AX nodes have no associated node or element in the DOM,

so the logic in AXObject::OnNativeClickAction doesn't do anything.

Now, this change attempts to fix this in two parts.



First, in AXObject::NativeClickAction, we will attempt to climb the

ancestor chain until we find a parent AXObject that has an element

if the current AXObject doesn't already have an element.



Second, we will give PseudoElements an AccessKeyAction() implementation

that just passes the request to the originating element. I felt weird

about this since the function name implies pseudo elements can have an

accesskey attribute which is only allowed on HTMLElements, but maybe

this is okay since SVGElements do the same thing?

entry.title: [ReduceToolbarUpdatesForSameDocNavigations] Fix cache
entry.content:
Two problems came from https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/4443727:



1. The urlbar sometimes displayed the wrong url because LocationBarModel is not properly tracking the state of being in a same

document navigation.



Sometimes we don't reset the flags after a same document navigation finishes, because the visible url was not updated and would cause onUrlChanged to exit early before getting to the reset logic. This change makes it so that the flags will always be reset

after a didFinishNavigation call. The cl fixes this by temporarily adds a new WebContentsObserver function that is called after the last onUrlUpdated() call.



2. The visibility of the back and forward buttons wouldn't be properly updated if the history was cleared and only same document navigations were performed afterwards. The cl fixes this by reverting to the previous behavior of always calling updateButtonStatus()

entry.title: [Autofill] Also TriggerReparse() in frames without seen form
entry.content:
FormForest::UpdateTreeOfRendererForm() triggers a reparse in the parent

frame if the parent form isn't known yet. This happens in the following

cases:

- The parent form has not (yet) been processed by

UpdateTreeOfRendererForm().

- The frame token has changed since the parent form has been extracted

and processed by UpdateTreeOfRendererForm().



Before this CL, TriggerReparse() was only done in frames for which

some form had been seen already. That is, TriggerReparse() was not

called

- in parent documents that are documents, or

- if FormsSeen() had not been executed for the parent frame, yet.



This CL triggers the reparse in the parent frame independent of whether

a form has been seen in it.



The motivation is just simplicity, especially once crrev.com/c/4499288

has removed //content dependencies from FormForest.



This comes at the cost of additional AutofillAgent::ProcessForms() calls

in the two cases mentioned above. A followup CL will address the

throttling of ProcessForms() to reduce duplicate work in the renderer.



Bug: 1187842, 1443645
